generated_description: tifran is an extreme sports club based in arilje, zlatibor administrative district, serbia. the club was founded by enthusiasts with a passion for the natural environment, who have gained their first rafting experiences on the lim, tara, and ibar rivers. tifran is named after the tifrančina waterfalls located in berana, which are among the most extreme in europe. the club participates in rafting events and competitions throughout serbia, montenegro, bosnia and herzegovina, and other regions in the balkans. membership is open to individuals aged 18 to 118, requiring a yearly membership fee and access to club equipment and participation in various activities.
